[Chorus]

For the A chord in the chorus do hammers and pull offs with your 4th finger on the
B string to get the effect of the little lead part in there.


   Jeremy spoke in    class               Today
   Dm               F    E    F             A
e|-1----------------1---------1-------------0-----------------------|
B|-3----------------1---------1------------h2-----------------------|
G|-2----------------2----1----2-------------2-----------------------|
D|-0----------------3----2----3-------------2-----------------------|
A|-----------------------2----3-------------0-----------------------|
E|-----------------------0----1-------------x-----------------------|

After the 2nd chorus when he first starts with "woo woo woo" (continuing on to) "trying
to forget this" play the first part of the verse like this

e|--------------------------------------------------------------------|
B|-------------0----0------------------0------------------------------|
G|-------------7----7------------------7----7-------------------------|
D|-------------0----5------------------0----5-------------------------|
A|-0--5--7--0-------0-----0--5--7--0--------0-------------------------|
E|--------------------------------------------------------------------|

Then when he gets to "board" Play F - G - A  until he repeats the "Jeremy spoke in" part.
When he does that do an F and G like this


F                G         F                 G          F
Jeremy spoke in  spoke in  Jeremy spoke in,  spoke in   Jeremy spoke in
G        A
class    today


Then repeat F - G - A  the rest of the song
   
